# Outreach updates — free-form dropbox

> **How this works:** Drop one update per bullet below (anything in a blockquote like this is ignored). Run `node tools/outreach/flush-updates.js` and it parses each line into structured changes on `outreach/leads.csv`.
>
> If `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` is set in `.env`, Claude Haiku parses with high accuracy.
> Without it, a regex fallback handles common patterns like "Name replied", "Name = dead", "call booked".
>
> Examples:
> - `Ernst replied, call today 16:30, email ernst@acme.com`
> - `Sarah = dead, not interested`
> - `NEW: https://linkedin.com/in/jane-doe — cold DM sent, source=manual_dm`
> - `John from Acme ghosted, move to dead`
>
> Unclear lines get left in this file for retry.

